  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ns/ontology/gist/exponentOfAmpere",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "DEFINITION: The exponent of ampere in a product of powers of base units."
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "EXAMPLE: In the equation '1 milliampere = 0.001 x ampere'\r\n\r\n\t\tthe conversionFactor for milliampere is 0.001\r\n\t\tthe exponent of ampere is 1\r\n\t\tall other exponents are zero\r\n\r\n\t\tEvery member of a unit group containing milliampere must be a multiple of ampere."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain": [
      {
        "@id": "_:b40bc5396184d9fb1"
      }
    ],
