        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "exponent of ampere"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range": [
      {
        "@id": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "The exponent of ampere in a product of powers of base units."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "In the equation '1 milliampere = 0.001 x ampere'\r\n\r\n\t\tthe conversionFactor for milliampere is 0.001\r\n\t\tthe exponent of ampere is 1\r\n\t\tall other exponents are zero\r\n\r\n\t\tEvery member of a unit group containing milliampere must be a multiple of ampere."
      }
